Polymorphism is the ability of the same method or function to behave differently for different objects.

method overrriding
class Animal:
    def sound(self):
        print("Animal makes a sound")

class Dog(Animal):
    def sound(self):
        print("Dog barks")

class Cat(Animal):
    def sound(self):
        print("Cat meows")

d = Dog()
c = Cat()

d.sound()
c.sound()


diff classes same methods
class Bird:
    def sound(self):
        print("Bird chirps")

class Lion:
    def sound(self):
        print("Lion roars")

b = Bird()
l = Lion()

b.sound()
l.sound()
